    "recap_headline": "South Dakota State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "TULSA, Okla. \u2014\u00a0For the second day in a row, Oral Roberts scored two runs in the bottom of the eighth inning to break a tie with South Dakota State in Summit League baseball action. Saturday afternoon at Chapman Park, the Golden Eagles' late rally gave them a 3-1 win and secured a series victory in the three-game set.\nORU improved to 9-9 overall and 2-0 in The Summit League. The Jackrabbits dropped to 5-13 overall and 0-2 in league play.\nTyler Brodrick started the game-winning rally in the eighth by drawing a one-out walk against\nAustin Henry\n. Left-hander\nTristan Augedahl\nthen entered and proceeded to hit the first batter he faced, Matthew Mainord, to put runners at first and second.\nORU then went to its bench for pinch-hitter Will Edmunson, who delivered by lining a single up the middle to drive in Brodrick and move Mainord to third. Hudson Ellis then plated an insurance run with a successful safety squeeze that brought in Mainord.\nThe Jackrabbits placed the tying run on base in the top of the ninth after\nNate Wachter\nreached on catcher's interference and\nCarter Taylor\nsingled. However, ORU closer Kash Ferris struck out the side, including the final two batters he faced, to earn the save.\nJackson Farrell picked up the win after allowing only one hit and striking out two in 2 1/3 shutout innings of relief. Starter Nathan Love worked the first \u00a05 1/3 innings, allowing a run on five hits while striking out three and walking two.\nORU was gifted a run in the bottom of the first inning as two consecutive Jackrabbit errors allowed the Golden Eagles to score the first run of the game.\nSDSU tied the game in the top of the third as\nNolan Grawe\ncame through with a two-out double to the right-center gap after\nLuke Wroblewski\ndrew a walk.\nJackrabbit starter\nSam Schlecht\ncontinued his strong senior campaign by not allowing an earned run in 5 2/3 innings. The right-hander gave up only four hits to go along with four strikeouts and two bases on balls. Henry entered with two men on in the bottom of the sixth and escaped the jam, but was assessed the loss after allowing the eventual game-winning run to reach base in the eighth.\nSDSU held a 7-5 advantage in hits, with its hits spread among seven different players. Nate Nichols was 2-for-3 to lead the Golden Eagles.\nON DECK\nThe series finale is slated for a 1 p.m. first pitch Sunday afternoon.\nNOTES\nORU leads the all-time series, 85-23, and has won the last 11 meetings\nThe Jackrabbits have scored a total of 10 runs during their current five-game losing streak\nHenry has allowed only three of 17 inherited runners (18 percent) to score in his nine appearances this season\nSchlecht lowered his season earned run average to 3.12 and upped his team-leading strikeout total to 26\nGrawe's double was his team-leading seventh of the season and the 19\nth\nof his career, which ranks as the most among active Jackrabbit players\n-GoJacks.com-"
